I've recently been reading _What We Owe the Future_ by William MacAskill.
It's my first foray into works related to effective altruism (EA), and also my
first introduction to longtermism. Intuitively, the math-based approach
EA takes to making a positive impact is very compelling, and yet I remain
curious about sorts of best and worst case results. Here, I attempt to place
mathematical bounds on utility produced from various scenarios centered around EA.

